name: Hawaii AG Holly T. Shikada
tweet: Hawai‘i Attorney General Holly T. Shikada joins the Jason Foundation’s fight against youth suicide. In Hawai‘i, suicide ranks as the 2nd leading cause of death for most middle and high school-age youth. For more info visit  https://t.co/o1J4TVCt5P

name: Hawaii AG Holly T. Shikada
tweet: Missing Child Center Hawai‘i supports scent-tracking K9s like Scout to help Hawai‘i County police recover missing children and endangered adults quickly and safely. Mahalo to Hawai‘i Island K9 Association and its supporters!  @Hawaii_Police @missingkids  https://t.co/0kYSkO8u8p  https://t.co/EhE45zZyOl

name: Hawaii AG Holly T. Shikada
tweet: Our Department is committed to #EndTrafficking by supporting victims and survivors, holding offenders accountable, and working with our partners in preventing  and combatting #HumanTrafficking in Hawaii. For help or to report call 888-373-7888 or text 233733  https://t.co/tIUgxARQlv

name: Hawaii AG Holly T. Shikada
tweet: Missing Child Center Hawaii is partnering again with the U.S. Department of Justice to promote the 39th National Missing Children’s Day Poster Contest.  Hawaii 5th graders can enter by 2/11/22.  See contest rules at  https://t.co/UBBtAAtORe  https://t.co/L2cAanwpmO
